%% Feast Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Admin
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Controller as Feast Operator<br/>Controller Manager
    participant Online as Online Feature Server<br/>6566/6567 TCP
    participant Offline as Offline Feature Server<br/>8815/8816 TCP
    participant Registry as Registry Server<br/>gRPC 6570/6571
    participant CronJob as CronJob Pod<br/>(ose-cli)
    participant ExternalDB as External DB Store<br/>(PostgreSQL/Redis/etc.)
    participant MLApp as ML Application

    Note over User,ExternalDB: Flow 1: Feature Store Deployment

    User->>K8sAPI: Create FeatureStore CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    K8sAPI->>Controller: Watch event<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Deployment, Services,<br/>ConfigMaps, PVCs, RBAC,<br/>CronJob, Route<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Resources created

    Note over User,ExternalDB: Flow 2: Online Feature Serving (Kubernetes Auth)

    MLApp->>Online: GET features<br/>443/TCP HTTPS<br/>TLS (service serving cert)<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA)
    Online->>K8sAPI: TokenReview + SubjectAccessReview<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>Online: Auth result
    Online->>Registry: Fetch feature metadata<br/>gRPC 6570/6571<br/>Optional TLS
    Registry-->>Online: Feature definitions
    Online->>ExternalDB: Read feature values<br/>Various ports/protocols<br/>Auth: DB credentials
    ExternalDB-->>Online: Feature data
    Online-->>MLApp: Feature response

    Note over User,ExternalDB: Flow 3: CronJob Materialization

    CronJob->>K8sAPI: kubectl exec into Feast pod<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI->>Online: Pod exec session<br/>Auth: RBAC (pods/exec)
    Online->>ExternalDB: feast materialize-incremental<br/>Read from offline, write to online<br/>Auth: DB credentials
    ExternalDB-->>Online: Materialized data
